(I'm Back, miss me?)

Now where were we?
Lunarpin growled , Predicons, he thought, the name meant nothing to him, yet
he felt this strange urge deep within himself to personally  chew up every
scrap of thier frames. To grind them up and recycle thier remanes into
"modern art". Somehow he knew his instincts weren't those of a wild wolf,
but those of a warrior whos fealt more than his share of losses. Did the
others Shadow Wing spoke of feal the same, or was it a simple character
malfunction? He had to know the truth.

"These others you mentioned? Lunarpine asked in a lost voice," Who are they?
Are they animals like us or are they still protoforms?" He didn't know
exactly what a "protoform" is but for an inexplicable reason the word fit.
